# Keep AiLang sources and the self-host seed LF on every platform.
#
# The bootstrap fixpoint (selfhost/bootstrap.sh) diffs the checked-in C seed
# byte-for-byte against the compiler's own codegen, which always emits LF. If a
# clone on Windows checks the seed out with CRLF — Git for Windows defaults to
# core.autocrlf=true — the diff fails spuriously even though nothing is wrong.
# Pinning these to LF makes `git clone` + bootstrap reproducible regardless of
# the user's autocrlf setting.
selfhost/seed/ailc.c text eol=lf
*.ail               text eol=lf
*.c                 text eol=lf
*.h                 text eol=lf
